items.title: Tanzania crackdown on planned protest leaves streets deserted
items.description: There is a large police presence in major cities and the authorities have encouraged people to stay home.

items.title: EU investigates Google over AI-generated summaries in search results
items.description: It is examining whether the tech giant did not offer "appropriate compensation" to web publishers.

items.title: Jakarta office fire kills at least 22, police confirm
items.description: The blaze in the Indonesian capital breaks out as office workers take their lunch break.

items.title: Burkina Faso accuses Nigerian Air Force of violating its airspace
items.description: Nigeria denies the violation saying the aircraft made an emergency landing due to a technical issue.

items.title: Nasa astronaut and cosmonauts return to Earth after 245 days in space
items.description: Nasa's Jonny Kim and cosmonauts Sergey Ryzhikov and Alexey Zubritsky have touched down in Earth after 245 days on the ISS.
